== 獎項和獎杯 ==
[[File:Gagarincup.gif|右]]
The winner of the playoff is awarded the [[Gagarin_Cup|Gagarin Cup]]. The highest placed Russian team is awarded the title of the Russian champion. The team ranked first in the standings after the regular season, i.e. the winner of the regular season, is awarded the [[Continental_Cup_(KHL)|Continental Cup]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://en.khl.ru/news/2010/3/5/23808.html |title=Ufa's first trophy |publisher=khl.ru |access-date=5 March 2010 |archive-date=2010-03-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100311180104/http://en.khl.ru/news/2010/3/5/23808.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> ({{lang-ru|Кубок Континента, Kubok Kontinenta}}). The winners of the [[KHL_Conference_Finals|conference finals]] are awarded the Eastern Conference Champion Cup ({{lang-ru|Кубок Победителю конференции Восток, Kubok Pobeditelyu konferentsii Vostok}}) and the Western Conference Champion Cup ({{lang-ru|Кубок Победителю конференции Запад, Kubok Pobeditelyu konferentsii Zapad}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.khl.ru/news/2010/3/4/26511.html |title=Новые трофеи Лиги |publisher=khl.ru |access-date=4 March 2010 |archive-date=2010-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100307143212/http://www.khl.ru/news/2010/3/4/26511.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

The KHL presents annual awards to its most successful players.  The KHL also awards the [[Opening_Cup|Opening Cup]] annually to the winner of the first game between the Gagarin Cup winner and the runner-up of the previous season. On 10 September 2011, three days after the [[Lokomotiv_Yaroslavl_plane_crash|Lokomotiv Yaroslavl plane crash]], the KHL head office decided to honor the deceased in the 2011 Opening Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.khl.ru/news/2012/09/05/43922.html|title=Официальное заявление КХЛ : Континентальная Хоккейная Лига (КХЛ)|access-date=13 May 2015|archive-date=2015-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402120650/http://www.khl.ru/news/2012/09/05/43922.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> The League gives the [[Andrey_Starovoytov|Andrey Starovoytov]] Award annually to its [[Official_(ice_hockey)|referee]]s of the year, also called the "Golden Whistle".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://scoutingtherefs.com/2018/05/22487/khl-olenin-sadovnikov-2018-golden-whistle/|title=KHL Names Olenin, Sadovnikov as 2018 Golden Whistle Winners|date=30 May 2018|website=Scouting the Refs|access-date=9 November 2018|archive-date=2021-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224162245/https://scoutingtherefs.com/2018/05/22487/khl-olenin-sadovnikov-2018-golden-whistle/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

